{"questionId":"17356","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\\left( x \\right) = \\frac{{2x - 4}}{{{x^2} - 1}}{\\text{, }} - 1 < x < 1\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>x</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,&nbsp;</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&lt;</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = f\\left( x \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>show that there are no <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>-intercepts.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2x - 4 = 0 \\Rightarrow x = 2\"> <mn>2</mn> <mi>x</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>4</mn> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>2</mn> </math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>outside the domain&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17356","referenceCode":"19N.1.AHL.TZ0.H_10b.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"show that there are no x -intercepts.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvaila